## 2. Technology Stack

### Backend
- **Runtime:** Python 3.10
- **Framework:** FastAPI (async-first)
- **ORM:** SQLAlchemy 2.0 (async sessions) + Alembic migrations
- **Validation:** Pydantic v2 (`model_validate`, not `parse_obj`)
- **Database:** SQLite — `data/pharmacy.db`

### Frontend
- **Framework:** React 19 + TypeScript (strict mode)
- **Build:** Vite
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS v3 (utility-only, no inline styles)
- **Components:** shadcn/ui (`src/components/ui/`)
- **HTTP:** axios via service layer (`src/services/`)

### Infrastructure
- **Deployment:** Docker + docker-compose (multi-stage builds)
- **Testing:** pytest + httpx (backend) | ESLint (frontend)

---

## 3. Architecture

**Pattern:** Repository → Service → API (strict layered separation)

### Backend Directory Layout
```
app/
  models/        # SQLAlchemy ORM models
  schemas/       # Pydantic request/response schemas
  repositories/  # Data access — one repository per model
  services/      # All business logic lives here, never in endpoints
  api/v1/endpoints/  # FastAPI route handlers (thin layer)
  core/          # Config, constants, custom exceptions
  db/            # Session factory and declarative base
```

### Frontend Directory Layout
```
src/
  pages/         # Route-level page components
  components/    # ui/ | common/ | forms/ | wizards/ | layout/
  hooks/         # Custom React hooks
  services/      # Axios API client modules
  types/         # TypeScript type definitions
  context/       # React context providers
  utils/         # cn(), formatters, constants
```

---

## 4. Code Style & Conventions

### Python (Backend)
- PEP 8 strict — type hints on **all** signatures and return values
- `from __future__ import annotations` for forward references
- Async database sessions with context managers
- One repository class per ORM model
- HTTP exceptions raised in **services**, propagated to FastAPI
- No business logic in endpoint handlers

### TypeScript / React (Frontend)
- `strict: true` — no `any` unless absolutely unavoidable
- Functional components + hooks only (no class components)
- RTL-first layout (`dir="rtl"` on body)
- Arabic labels with English code identifiers
- `cn()` from `src/utils/cn.ts` for all class merging
- Controlled form components; state managed locally or in context
- All API calls through `src/services/` — never directly from components

### Universal
- No comments unless explaining non-obvious logic
- No `console.log` in production code
- No `TODO` without a linked GitHub issue
- File naming: `snake_case.py` for Python, `PascalCase.tsx` for React components
- Imports ordered: external libraries → internal modules

